# Architecture Rules (AI Frontend Architecture v3)

The project follows **AI Frontend Architecture v3**.

The architecture separates UI generation and feature logic.

UI is generated using **Atomic Design**.
Application structure follows **Feature-Sliced Design (FSD)**.

Atomic UI components must be placed in:

shared/ui

Feature logic must be placed in:

features/

Pages must only compose widgets.

Widgets must compose features and entities.

---

# Folder Structure

src
├ app
├ pages
├ widgets
├ features
├ entities
└ shared
└ ui

---

# Responsibility Separation

Designer

- generates Atomic UI components
- maintains design system

Developer

- implements feature logic
- manages state and API
- maintains application architecture

---

# Important Rules

UI components must not contain business logic.

Feature logic must not be implemented inside shared/ui.

Entities represent domain models.

Widgets compose UI blocks using entities and features.

Pages compose widgets only.
